Routine care provided: observation or post-resuscitation, according to risk factors at birth and neonatal resuscitation. • Routine care: the newborn is vigorous, without risk factors, and the airway clear. Should not be separated from its mother • Observation Care: for newborns with antenatal or intrapartum risk factors and skin is dyed or with meconium, respiration or activity is poor and / or cyanosis, requiring careful attention. • Post resuscitation care: the infants who required positive pressure ventilation or more complex neonatal resuscitation, require continuous care and are at high risk of developing complications and an abnormal transition

15 Oxygen administered at 6L by nasal catheter or placed on mechanical ventilator.
16 Timely referral to higher level resolution (ICU).
